      <back>
         <div type="commentary">
            <p>Erosion prevents a definitive reading of the names on the epitaph; those suggested in this 
               interpretation are attested elsewhere and are thus possible here. A line at the top of the 
               stone, which appears to be a border, negates the possibility of a standard θάρσει ("be of 
               good courage") preceding the first line here. Dimensions refer to entire remainder of stone.</p>
         </div>
